[5] Venezuela
Date: 1 Dec 2005
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Alerta Epidemiologico, Semana Epidemiologica 46, Ministerio de
Salud, Venezuela, 13-19 Nov 2005 MSDS, [trans. Mod.JGM; edited]
<http://www.msds.gov.ve/msds/Boletines/Alertas/2005/Alerta46.zip>

During the current epidemiological week, 838 dengue fever cases were
diagnosed, 62 of which (7.4 percent) were dengue hemorrhagic fever; the
dengue fever/dengue hemorrhagic fever ratio is 13/1. Cumulated case toll
for 2005 is 37 684 cases, 6.3 percent of which are dengue hemorrhagic fever
(2370 cases); the dengue fever/dengue hemorrhagic fever ratio is 15/1.
Cumulated morbidity rate is 141.8 per 100 000 inhabitants. Circulating
serotypes are 1, 2, 3, and 4. Cumulated case toll for this period shows a
36.3 percent increase compared to the same period of 2004. This week no
dengue-related deaths have been reported.
An 11.0 percent reduction in the number of dengue cases compared to figures
for last week was observed, and the epidemiological situation still
corresponds to an epidemic. Persons less than 15 years old make up 53.1
percent of all notified cases; persons 15 to 24 years old are the 2nd most
affected group, with 20.0 percent of all cases. Federal Regions reporting
highest cases figures are as follows: Capital District (82), Miranda (80),
Barinas (78), Merida (72), Lara (62), and Tachira (62).
--
